div.div:
System events:
UserCreated - emitted after the user has been authorized and saved in db
IngestChannel - emited either by scheduled job or when new channel has been discovered and saved to db
VideoCreated - emitted after video was discovered and saved to our db
VideoDownloadStarted - emitted after start of download from youtube
VideoDownloadFailed - emitted in case when download from youtube failed, should contain reason
VideoDownloadSucceded - emitted in case of successful download from youtube
VideoUploadToJoystreamStarted - emitted when JoystreamUploader picked up video and started upload to network
VideoUploadToJoystreamFailed - emitted in case of upload to jooystream network failure, should contain reason if possible
VideoUploadToJoystreamSucceded - emitted in case of successful upload to joystream network

div.div:
Frequency - defines how often we ingest the content. It is measured in minutes,e.g. 60 - means that given channel will be ingested every hour, 1440 - every 24 hours and so on.
This gives us the ability to ingest channels with more subscribers, videos etc.
The abstract frequency formula is following - f(subscribers, videosCount, viewsCount, timeSinceAdded) -> value in range [t1, t2] - where t1 is the system wide lower bound for frequency, t2 - system wide upper bound for frequency
The relative weight for each property to de decided
